products.name: Canada Brooch
products.description:
Prime Minister Justin Trudeau sums up Canada best:
"From dogsledding in the Northwest Territories to surfing in Tofino, from the history of Old Quebec to the vibrancy of multicultural Toronto, from breathtakingly empty prairie skies to the warm welcome on George St in St John's, from the thrill of skiing in the Rockies to the serenity of paddling past a moose in Algonquin Park-there's nowhere else on earth that offers the range of adventures that await you in Canada."
Home of hockey and Tim Hortons, 2017 marks the 150th anniversary of Canada's Confederation, making it 150 years we've been on the "eh" team.
These brooches are laser cut from oak plywood, about 2 inches in height. They have hand painted details and are finished with a varnish sealant with a silver c clasp brooch pin. Due to the handmade nature of this item, each piece will be slightly different from another.
All pieces are designed and produced by myself at my home studio in St. John's, Newfoundland.

products.name: Labrador Brooch - Natural
products.description:
The Newfoundland and Labrador Labrador Region page says it the best:
"Labrador, The Big Land, one of the last untamed, unspoiled places left on earth. It stretches from the Strait of Belle Isle in the south, to Cape Chidley in the far north, boasting towering mountains, massive rock faces and an infinite supply of lakes and rivers, not to mention waters seasonally teeming with whales and icebergs. Here, you'll find plenty of fresh air, crystal clear water and truly authentic people."
It's a place that those who call home love fiercely, and a place that visitors wish they could call home. No matter if you're a Livyer or a CFA (Come From Away), with this Labrador map brooch showcasing Labrador City, you can take a little piece of The Big Land with you wherever you go.
These brooches are laser cut from oak plywood, about 2 inches in height. They have hand painted details and are finished with a varnish sealant with a silver c clasp brooch pin. Due to the handmade nature of this item, each piece will be slightly different from another.
All pieces are designed and produced by myself at my home studio in St. John's, Newfoundland.

products.name: Puffin Brooch
products.description:
Beautiful maple stained Atlantic puffin earrings laser cut from Baltic birch. 
The Atlantic puffin is the official bird of our home province of Newfoundland and Labrador. These little seabirds are only found in the Atlantic ocean and come to Newfoundland each year to nest. 
Just like the rest of us Newfoundlanders, though we may roam far from home, we always find our way back. 
Standing at just about an inch high, these little birds are on nickel-free, silver finish posts and although they are post backed stud earrings, they are long and do dangle a little bit.

products.name: Partridgeberry Earrings
products.description:
Berry picking is a well-loved tradition in Newfoundland. No need to go to a farm or a u-pick, just grab a bucket or two and wander out into the woods and pick your own! 
We've got orange bakeapples (also known as cloudberries outside of Newfoundland), red partridgeberries (also known as lingonberries outside of Newfoundland), and of course, blue blueberries! 
These earrings are laser cut from Baltic birch plywood, about half an inch in height, handpainted, and finished with a varnish sealant. The posts and backs are silver plated and nickel free. Due to the handmade nature of this item, each piece will be slightly different from another. 
All pieces are designed and produced by myself at my home studio in St. John's, Newfoundland.

products.name: Whale Tail Earrings
products.description:
Newfoundland is one of the best places to go whale watching in the world, with people flocking to Newfoundland in hopes of a glimpse of that iconic whale tail. With over 22 species of whale visiting our coasts between May and September, these majestic beasts frolick and play in our waters, creating a spectacle for us to enjoy. 
From minke whales to blue whales and even orca, Newfoundland is also home to the world's largest population of humpbacks. The humpback fluke is a common sight on our shores, and is represented here in this earring!
These earrings are laser cut from maple plywood, about an inch in height, and finished with a varnish sealant. The posts and backs are silver plated and nickel free. Due to the handmade nature of this item, each piece will be slightly different from another.
All pieces are designed and produced by myself at my home studio in St. John's, Newfoundland.

products.name: Best Kind Keychain
products.description:
BEST KIND
Translation: General approval; in the best state or condition.
Influenced by mostly Western England and Southern Island accents (with a little French and Aboriginal thrown in), there are more varieties of English spoken in Newfoundland and Labrador than anywhere else in the world. 
It's more than just accents too: we've got our very own dictionary and encyclopedia. The Dictionary of Newfoundland English was first published in 1982 and contains hundreds of words and phrases you'll find nowhere else.
These keychains are laser cut from oak plywood, about 2 inches in height. They are finished with a varnish sealant with a silver finish keychain. Due to the handmade nature of this item, each piece will be slightly different from another.
All pieces are designed and produced by myself at my home studio in St. John's, Newfoundland.

products.name: RowHouse Magnet
products.description:
Lovingly nicknamed Jellybean Row, colourful row houses line the streets of downtown St Johns. Green, blue, purple, red, orange... Every colour you can imagine, sometimes matching, sometimes clashing, combined with sloping hills all come together to create a unique visual you're not likely to find anywhere else. 
These magnets are laser cut from maple plywood, about 2 inches in height. They have hand painted details and are finished with a varnish sealant with magnet on the back. All pieces are designed and produced by myself at my home studio in St. John's, Newfoundland.
